title: I LOVE LISTS
description: I LOVE LISTS  It’s time to plant leeks and onions. How Oprah likes her eggs.  Some dark history facts if you’re into that sorta thing. One day I will make a pumpkin roll. Close-up photographer of the year.  Weather photographer of the year. My mom always ran into friends while traveling. What’s the swish & swipe cleaning method? I am obsessed with these dioramas!  You can pretend you live in Studio Ghibli world.  How to get stains out of tupperware.  One-legged comedian has fun with Halloween costumes. Time travel to Paris in the 1960s. So many food superstitions!  Clothesline illusions are playful. Sweater tunics! one / two / three  How to maximize your vacation days next year. Andrew Garfield talks about grief on Sesame Street.  Old Taco Bell items, ranked. I hope to finish this audiobook this weekend!  How’s your grief this season? Need a grief buddy? MC and I are here for you! Keep Grief Weird!  My currently workbooks are going to be in my shop soon! Stay tuned! Help me help you! Here are some deals!  Here’s 40% off your first Thrive Market order.  – I saved $450 last year!  Use my affiliate link to get a free month of Skillshare premium!  Want extra discounts and cashback on online purchases? I use Rakuten religiously!  The post I LOVE LISTS appeared first on Shutterbean.
